
[1]premeditate

   PREMED'ITATE, v.t. [L. proemeditor; proe, before, and meditor, to
   mediate.] To think on and revolve in the mind beforehand; to contrive
   and design previously; as, to premeditate theft or robbery.

   With words premeditated thus he said.

        PREMED'ITATE, v.i. To think, consider or revolve in the mind
      beforehand; to deliberate; to have formed in the mind by previous
                           thought or meditation.

             PREMED'ITATE, a. Contrived by previous meditation.
